- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling musical pieces as complex networks and clustering them. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a likely category as the paper deals with analyzing networks and their metrics. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper deals with categorizing music. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper deals with grouping similar musical tracks. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category but still possible as the paper mentions applications in multimedia domains such as music didactics and multimedia entertainment.
